  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\n12th Gen I7 CPU\r\n64 GB DDR4 Ram\r\n16 TB NVMe SSD on ZFS RaidZ1 pool with LZ4 compression\r\n\r\nErigon version: ./erigon --version: erigon version 2022.99.99-dev\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Debian 11.2 x86-64\r\n\r\nCommit hash : Initial sync on 47df98a4992690ca5e9af874f14e3f7088551a91 still persists on b6f707d8119667f13a069082b432c800def6da3f\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nBor mainnet (Polygon) would fully sync and stay synced.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nHalfway through the sync erigon starts to blow up in memory usage which results in erigon getting killed by the OOM killer and the process to repeat.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nAttempt to sync a full node running the following command:\r\n\r\nerigon --datadir /zfs_pool/polygon --private.api.addr=localhost:9092 --port 30304 --chain bor-mainnet --watch-the-burn\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nAttached as file, too large to post in the body of a bug report.\r\n[Erigon-Bor-Backtrace.txt](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/files/8253712/Erigon-Bor-Backtrace.txt)\r\n\r\n\r\nI can make available the datadir of this node to any developers on the Erigon team, reach out to me on Discord and I will provide you a download link (be aware compressed it will still be 500~800 GB).",
